args: If we don't defeat this thing quickly,\nit's going to send us flying!
We picked a lousy foe to run into\nwhen the footin' is this bad!
Oh no... I'm losing my balance!
Nnngh... Wh-where are we? I remember\nus falling over that cliff, and then...\nWait, where is Alfonse?
Thank goodness! Are you all right?
Not quite—I've hurt my foot, which is\nmaking walking difficult. I suggest you\nleave me behind and go on alone.
That is NOT going to happen.\nHere, climb on my back.
I don't think that's wise. We might run into\nfiends or imperial soldiers on the way out.
If that happens, I will only be a burden.
It makes more sense for you to\ngo on alone and return with aid.
I'm not doing that. We don't even know\nwhere we ARE, which means we have no\nidea how long it'll take for help to come.
You are an individual who can—and\nshould—change the world around him.
I can't allow someone like that to be\nhurt—or worse—in an effort to save\nsomeone not even from this world.
I could say the same to you!
You have a goal you need to accomplish\nin your own world, right?
Well, that means I can't let any harm\ncome to you in mine.
Especially since you're the one who\nrescued me when I was almost sent flying.
You saved my life, Alfonse.\nLet me return the favor.
Besides, I'm not going to let anything\nhappen to you OR me. You'll just have\nto trust me on that.
*pant* Let's stop and rest here for a bit.
My apologies again for burdening you,\nPrince {player_name}.
You are responsible for the future of\nthis entire country, yet you chose the\nmost dangerous course of action.
If the most dangerous course of action\nalso happens to be the best, I don't\nhave a problem with that.
This might be a bit irresponsible to say,\nbut the title of ＂prince＂ doesn't really\nmatter to me.
Even with the title, I'm still a person—\nand people all have their own wishes\nand ways of thinking.
The only thing I care about is that\neveryone lives in peace and happiness.
Hmm. All this time, I was thinking we\nhad little in common. But now—
Well, look who we have here...
What's the imperial army doing here?!
We heard the traitorous prince lost his\nfooting and fell from a cliff, and have\nbeen searching for you ever since.

To be frank, the rumor sounded inane;
what kind of prince falls off a CLIFF?
Yet here you are—and your head will
make a fine decoration for our castle gate!
Aaah ha ha! Do you honestly think you\ncan escape us with that sack of potatoes\ndraped across your back?
Seize them, men! Don't damage the head\nof the prince, but do whatever you like\nto this other one!
I won't let you touch him! Haaaah!
Blast... There's no end to them!
Such a shame to see a beautiful friendship\nlike yours ended so soon... Aaaah ha ha!
Urk... Did you really just tackle a man in\nthe middle of swinging his weapon?\nYou must really wanna die!
In that case, I'm happy to oblige!
We've been searchin' for ya for ages!\nBut this lets us make a kick-butt entrance\nto save the day, so I'm good with it.
Showing up in times of need is what\nfriends do, right? Now let's get 'em!
We don't stand a chance... Retreat!
We've been walking from our original\nlocation for hours. How did you find us?
Easy—we just sent everybody in the\nentire castle out to look for you!
It is a good thing we made it in time.
Stay still, Alfonse. I'll heal you.
I can't believe you tried to tackle an\narmed man. Why would you do something\nso incredibly reckless?!
You're one to talk about recklessness.\nBesides, it was a calculated risk—though\none with admittedly low odds of success.
I simply couldn't stand the thought\nof losing someone important to me.
Thank you for saying that—\nand thank you for saving me.
Thank you ALL for saving me.\nI've been blessed with great friends.
Now I just need to get stronger, so we can\nall make a world where everyone is happy.
